WEBVTT

00:10.468 --> 00:14.431
[Leroy]<i> I can't breathe. I wasn't put</i>
<i>on this planet to point a freakin' camera</i>

00:14.514 --> 00:16.266
<i>at a freakin' wedding cake.</i>

00:19.436 --> 00:21.771
<i>I keep thinking about</i> Close Encounters.

00:23.148 --> 00:27.694
<i>At the end, Richard Dreyfuss,</i>
<i>he says goodbye to Earth</i>

00:27.986 --> 00:29.904
<i>and he gets on that UFO.</i>

00:30.572 --> 00:31.906
<i>He has to.</i>

00:33.742 --> 00:36.161
<i>Gotta say goodbye</i>
<i>to your friends and family...</i>

00:37.579 --> 00:39.956
[sighs]<i> ...for the great unknown.</i>

00:41.249 --> 00:43.960
<i>That's a hero. That's an artist.</i>

00:44.544 --> 00:48.047
<i>And a real artist doesn't need friends</i>
<i>or family.</i>

01:30.882 --> 01:32.133
[panting]

01:34.677 --> 01:37.096
["The Freshmen" by The Verve Pipe playing]

01:47.357 --> 01:48.817
[Jessica]<i> Don't forget, Beavers,</i>

01:48.900 --> 01:51.444
Intergalactic Lust
<i>premieres tomorrow night.</i>

01:51.528 --> 01:53.988
<i>Be there or be square.</i>

01:54.531 --> 01:57.283
<i>♪ When I was young I knew everything ♪</i>

01:58.785 --> 02:02.205
<i>♪ And she a punk</i>
<i>Who rarely ever took advice ♪</i>

02:02.288 --> 02:03.873
<i>Why are you here?</i>

02:04.666 --> 02:06.334
[Luke]<i> And, cut.</i>

02:06.417 --> 02:07.293
[sighs]

02:08.628 --> 02:13.716
<i>♪ Stop a baby's breath</i>
<i>And a shoe full of rice, no ♪</i>

02:14.092 --> 02:17.387
[Luke]<i> Hey, everyone, big ups to Kate</i>
<i>for making this all happen.</i>

02:17.470 --> 02:19.305
[all cheering]

02:20.598 --> 02:23.852
<i>♪ 'Cause she was touching her face ♪</i>

02:25.353 --> 02:28.815
<i>♪ I won't be held responsible ♪</i>

02:29.440 --> 02:31.860
<i>-♪ She fell in love in the first place ♪</i>
-[phone ringing]

02:31.943 --> 02:33.862
<i>Pocket residence, Scott speaking.</i>

02:33.945 --> 02:35.280
Hey, pal, it's Luke O'Neil.

02:36.114 --> 02:38.533
Cedric, hey, my man.

02:38.825 --> 02:41.119
I know the screening is tonight, Leslie.

02:41.911 --> 02:43.079
I need your help.

02:47.000 --> 02:50.128
-T-This changes the whole movie.
-I know. That's the idea.

02:50.211 --> 02:53.673
How's that gonna work? Premiere's tonight,
you're out of time, homes.

02:53.756 --> 02:57.051
I'm only out of time
when the lights go down. And...

02:59.304 --> 03:00.305
Action!

03:00.388 --> 03:01.389
<i>♪ Valium and slept ♪</i>

03:01.472 --> 03:05.101
<i>♪ Now he's guilt stricken sobbing ♪</i>

03:05.184 --> 03:06.436
You're wise to come around.

03:06.519 --> 03:09.397
-Think you got it?
-Ain't no thing, but a chicken wing.

03:10.690 --> 03:12.191
[Luke] And...

03:12.775 --> 03:13.610
Action!

03:13.693 --> 03:16.613
<i>♪ I can't be held responsible ♪</i>

03:18.656 --> 03:21.367
<i>♪ 'Cause she was touching her face ♪</i>

03:23.286 --> 03:26.623
<i>♪ I won't be held responsible ♪</i>

03:27.665 --> 03:29.918
[Leslie]<i> Can I tell McQuaid</i>
<i>you're changing the movie?</i>

03:30.001 --> 03:30.877
[Luke]<i> No.</i>

03:31.252 --> 03:32.337
Can I tell Kate?

03:32.420 --> 03:34.422
Especially not Kate.

03:34.505 --> 03:35.757
Can I tell Tyler?

03:35.840 --> 03:39.302
No one can know about this.
It has to be a surprise. Okay?

03:39.385 --> 03:40.220
Okay.

03:41.262 --> 03:44.724
<i>♪ For the life of me I cannot believe ♪</i>

03:44.807 --> 03:45.767
Roll sound.

03:45.850 --> 03:49.979
<i>♪ We'd ever die for these sins</i>
<i>We were merely freshmen ♪</i>

03:50.313 --> 03:55.151
<i>♪ For the life of me I cannot remember ♪</i>

03:55.235 --> 03:58.196
<i>Know this, I'm better for loving you.</i>

03:58.279 --> 04:00.531
<i>♪ We'd never compromise ♪</i>

04:00.615 --> 04:04.077
<i>♪ For the life of me I cannot believe ♪</i>

04:04.160 --> 04:08.873
<i>♪ We'd ever die for these sins</i>
<i>We were merely freshmen ♪</i>

04:22.095 --> 04:23.012
[Leslie] Enjoy.

04:24.597 --> 04:27.642
-Are you Luke's Mom?
-Yeah, yeah, I am. [chuckles]

04:28.351 --> 04:29.811
I will show you to your seat.

04:30.603 --> 04:32.563
Okay. Thank you.

04:33.606 --> 04:35.358
It's still a little soggy up here.

04:36.567 --> 04:37.652
Follow me.

04:49.706 --> 04:52.375
-Hey, good-looking.
-[chuckles] Hey.

04:53.084 --> 04:54.043
Nice dress.

04:54.127 --> 04:55.962
Oh, thank you.

04:56.045 --> 04:58.256
Somebody might have helped me pick it out.

04:58.881 --> 04:59.882
[chuckles]

05:02.302 --> 05:03.928
You pierced your nose.

05:04.637 --> 05:07.890
Yep, somebody might have inspired me.

05:09.642 --> 05:10.893
I got you something.

05:16.941 --> 05:18.109
It matches your nails.

05:18.443 --> 05:20.236
[Kate] Oh... [chuckles] yeah.

05:20.778 --> 05:22.071
Thanks.

05:23.781 --> 05:25.867
So, do you want to sit together?

05:26.993 --> 05:28.786
Doesn't that go without saying?

05:28.870 --> 05:29.954
Of course!

05:30.038 --> 05:33.207
Yeah, totally. I just didn't know
if you wanted to sit with me,

05:33.291 --> 05:35.418
or sit alone, 'cause that would be--

05:35.501 --> 05:36.461
[chuckles] Kate...

05:38.129 --> 05:39.589
I want to sit with you.

05:40.256 --> 05:41.424
Cheers.

05:46.721 --> 05:51.392
You're to sit in the front row,
next to the gentleman.

06:00.109 --> 06:01.486
Enjoy the show.

06:11.079 --> 06:12.538
-Hi.
-Hi.

06:13.331 --> 06:15.333
[stammering] I can move if you prefer.

06:16.459 --> 06:18.878
No. No, that's okay.

06:20.713 --> 06:22.757
Did Luke send you up here?

06:23.674 --> 06:24.550
Yeah.

06:30.556 --> 06:31.599
Popcorn?

06:32.850 --> 06:36.145
-Are you sure you have enough to share?
-Hmm. No.

06:36.229 --> 06:37.730
No popcorn for you.

06:37.814 --> 06:38.981
[Sherry chuckles]

06:44.070 --> 06:45.363
How are you?

06:47.448 --> 06:49.784
I... I've been better.

06:50.910 --> 06:51.869
You?

06:52.453 --> 06:53.746
Same.

06:59.252 --> 07:01.045
[equipment creaking]

07:04.882 --> 07:06.634
S-s-so, you nervous?

07:06.717 --> 07:11.180
Nervousness is an irrational feeling that
has no practical application whatsoever.

07:11.264 --> 07:12.682
So, y-you nervous?

07:12.765 --> 07:14.142
Very much so, yes.

07:14.225 --> 07:15.852
Yeah, I thought so.

07:15.935 --> 07:17.061
Dude, she's here.

07:17.145 --> 07:21.357
McQuaid, good-looking tux.

07:21.816 --> 07:22.942
Where'd you get it?

07:23.025 --> 07:26.112
Oh, this old thing's...
It's been in my family for years.

07:26.195 --> 07:27.321
Really?

07:27.405 --> 07:30.575
-I saw the same one at the thrift store.
-No.

07:30.658 --> 07:32.201
No, I don't think so.

07:33.161 --> 07:34.120
Mm-hmm.

07:52.847 --> 07:54.140
[exhales]

07:56.309 --> 07:57.560
I'm ready.

07:58.436 --> 08:00.271
Cue spotlight.

08:11.199 --> 08:12.325
[clears throat]

08:13.367 --> 08:14.452
Hello.

08:14.535 --> 08:15.912
I'm Luke O'Neil.

08:17.663 --> 08:19.499
Thank you all for coming.

08:21.626 --> 08:23.419
This guy I once knew

08:23.503 --> 08:27.465
said that in order to be an artist,
you couldn't be held back by things.

08:29.217 --> 08:31.093
Things like friends or family.

08:31.886 --> 08:35.097
I don't know. The reason
I bring this up now is because it's...

08:35.681 --> 08:37.225
it's helped me realize something.

08:38.851 --> 08:41.187
That guy was one hundred percent wrong.

08:42.563 --> 08:47.109
It's because of my friends and my family
that I've been able to make this movie.

08:48.152 --> 08:49.779
This is our movie.

08:51.447 --> 08:55.201
And, uh, I want to thank everyone
from Drama Club to A/V Club,

08:55.284 --> 08:56.786
to Stargrove.

08:56.869 --> 08:57.787
What's up, man?

08:57.870 --> 09:01.332
But, most importantly,
I want to thank Mr. Messner.

09:03.334 --> 09:06.671
Thank you for allowing us to go to Cali.

09:06.754 --> 09:09.966
And for what it's worth,
I think you're a really good dude.

09:10.925 --> 09:12.093
[audience] Aw!

09:16.013 --> 09:17.348
[Luke] All right.

09:18.140 --> 09:19.517
Enjoy the movie, everyone.

09:29.026 --> 09:31.320
<i>Greetings, my friends.</i>

09:31.404 --> 09:33.573
<i>We are all interested in the future,</i>

09:33.656 --> 09:38.452
<i>for that is where you and I</i>
<i>are going to spend the rest of our lives.</i>

09:38.828 --> 09:41.622
<i>You will now witness the shocking tale</i>

09:41.706 --> 09:44.709
<i>of a literal star-crossed love affair...</i>

09:44.792 --> 09:45.710
Is this new?

09:45.793 --> 09:47.253
<i>...light-years from now.</i>

09:47.962 --> 09:51.173
<i>The story of a man so unfortunate</i>

09:51.257 --> 09:56.095
<i>as to fall in love</i>
<i>with the most forbidden of alien kind.</i>

09:56.804 --> 09:59.974
<i>My friends, the moment has come.</i>

10:00.725 --> 10:02.893
<i>Can your hearts withstand</i>

10:03.227 --> 10:06.022
<i>the shocking tale that is</i>

10:06.105 --> 10:08.441
Intergalactic Lust?

10:12.236 --> 10:13.529
[clears throat]

10:13.613 --> 10:16.866
<i>As you, my fellow Americans, well know,</i>

10:16.949 --> 10:20.786
<i>improving the space program</i>
<i>has been important to my administration.</i>

10:21.120 --> 10:25.666
<i>Which is why I'm confident that not only</i>
<i>will we reach Mars and Jupiter,</i>

10:25.750 --> 10:30.004
<i>but we will also manage to reach...</i>
<i>Uranus.</i>

10:31.589 --> 10:32.715
[male student] Duh!

10:32.798 --> 10:34.842
[audience giggles]

10:34.925 --> 10:38.012
<i>-President, I need your attention.</i>
<i>-What, Secret Agent Smith?</i>

10:38.095 --> 10:40.765
<i>Aliens from planet Gloptonia have landed</i>
<i>on Earth.</i>

10:40.848 --> 10:43.309
<i>It appears they have touched down</i>
<i>in Boring, Oregon.</i>

10:43.392 --> 10:44.435
<i>Boring?</i>

10:45.019 --> 10:46.896
<i>Who would name their town Boring?</i>

10:46.979 --> 10:48.189
[student blows raspberry]

10:48.272 --> 10:50.399
[Cedric]<i> There is no time.</i>
<i>We must act now.</i>

10:50.483 --> 10:51.901
[Jessica]<i> You're right.</i>

10:52.568 --> 10:55.780
<i>Smith, I want you</i>
<i>and all my agents in the field, now!</i>

10:56.280 --> 10:57.573
[male student] Penis!

10:57.657 --> 10:59.325
[audience laughs]

11:00.868 --> 11:02.411
[student] God, this movie sucks.

11:02.495 --> 11:04.664
[audience laughs]

11:12.546 --> 11:13.964
[sighs]

11:17.927 --> 11:21.138
<i>Blorg, please do not leave me</i>
<i>and go to Earth.</i>

11:21.222 --> 11:22.681
<i>I love you.</i>

11:22.765 --> 11:23.974
<i>Why must you leave me?</i>

11:24.058 --> 11:25.643
<i>Please don't leave me.</i>

11:25.726 --> 11:30.064
[Oliver]<i> I must join my comrades</i>
<i>to defeat the Earthlings for their cheese.</i>

11:30.147 --> 11:32.483
<i>Farewell, my love.</i>

11:32.566 --> 11:35.820
<i>Perhaps for now, perhaps forever.</i>

11:36.320 --> 11:37.446
[door closes]

11:44.412 --> 11:46.205
[laughing]

11:50.709 --> 11:52.294
[Cedric]<i> The aliens are up ahead!</i>

11:52.878 --> 11:54.422
[machine beeping]

11:59.718 --> 12:01.720
[students]<i> Whoo!</i>

12:03.139 --> 12:05.182
[Cedric]<i> Greetings, fair one.</i>

12:05.933 --> 12:07.017
[students]<i> Whoo!</i>

12:08.269 --> 12:09.478
<i>Zarginda!</i>

12:09.562 --> 12:11.480
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

12:14.650 --> 12:17.862
<i>Who's the human?</i>
<i>Seems you two got along well enough.</i>

12:17.945 --> 12:20.114
<i>Blorg! No, never.</i>

12:20.197 --> 12:22.241
<i>I could never love an Earthling!</i>

12:22.324 --> 12:24.702
<i>If you did, I'd blow their planet to bits!</i>

12:25.077 --> 12:28.330
<i>-You'd do well to remember that.</i>
-[Emaline] <i>Look out!</i>

12:28.414 --> 12:31.667
<i>We're heading straight</i>
<i>toward asteroid belt B-13!</i>

12:31.750 --> 12:35.254
<i>Its poisonous gas has been known</i>
<i>to have shape-shifting properties</i>

12:35.337 --> 12:37.047
<i>that work on males only!</i>

12:37.798 --> 12:38.924
[Emaline shrieks]

12:39.008 --> 12:39.967
[audience laughs]

12:40.676 --> 12:42.553
-[Emaline gasps]
-[audience laughs]

12:42.636 --> 12:44.388
[McQuaid]<i> Oh my, I feel strange.</i>

12:44.472 --> 12:46.015
<i>Has my appearance changed?</i>

12:47.141 --> 12:50.019
-This is pretty fun.
-Oh, my God, it's good, right?

12:52.229 --> 12:55.024
[Emaline]<i> Someone's stealing</i>
<i>the Saturn Five rocket.</i>

12:55.107 --> 12:57.276
<i>It's him! Stop him!</i>

12:57.359 --> 12:59.028
[McQuaid]<i> What I do, I do for love!</i>

12:59.111 --> 13:00.362
<i>Victorious!</i>

13:00.446 --> 13:05.534
<i>Cheesemongers of Earth shall rue the day</i>
<i>they provoked the mighty Blorg.</i>

13:05.868 --> 13:09.371
[Emaline]<i> Bound by duty and love,</i>
<i>I say you're more god than Gloptonite.</i>

13:12.583 --> 13:14.418
[audience]<i> </i>Whoo! [cheering]

13:14.502 --> 13:19.423
[audience applauding and whooping]

13:21.592 --> 13:23.344
So hot, McQuaid!

13:25.554 --> 13:30.100
[Tyler]<i> Commander Blorg, this human</i>
<i>was found by an abandoned space pod.</i>

13:30.476 --> 13:33.103
[McQuaid]<i> Thank you, Vakes.</i>
<i>So, tell me, human.</i>

13:33.187 --> 13:36.357
<i>What brings you to Gloptonia,</i>
<i>you mortal fool?</i>

13:39.527 --> 13:40.402
<i>Her.</i>

13:40.486 --> 13:42.738
[audience cheering]

13:43.072 --> 13:46.033
<i>You heard me, I'm here for your woman,</i>
<i>you nasty-ass Muppet!</i>

13:46.825 --> 13:49.453
-[audience exclaims]
-[yells]

13:50.371 --> 13:54.625
-[screaming]
-[thuds]

13:55.626 --> 13:58.045
-[splats]
-[McQuaid]<i> Vakes!</i>

13:58.128 --> 14:00.589
[laughing]

14:07.888 --> 14:11.100
<i>Let's leave this place</i>
<i>and live happily ever after on Earth.</i>

14:11.183 --> 14:14.770
<i>Definitely. We can't--</i>
<i>I... I can't make you do this.</i>

14:15.479 --> 14:19.692
<i>You couldn't survive on Earth</i>
<i>and I-I can't survive here.</i>

14:19.775 --> 14:21.318
<i>We both know it.</i>

14:21.402 --> 14:25.990
<i>I didn't want to believe it,</i>
<i>but we don't choose who we are, Zarginda.</i>

14:26.365 --> 14:28.576
<i>We belong in different worlds,</i>

14:28.659 --> 14:31.662
<i>and it breaks my heart</i>
<i>we're not meant to be,</i>

14:31.745 --> 14:34.415
<i>but I'm better for loving you.</i>

14:35.624 --> 14:40.546
[sighs]<i> And if you even feel</i>
<i>one percent the same way...</i>

14:42.298 --> 14:43.799
<i>that's enough for me.</i>

14:55.853 --> 14:59.064
Luke, why aren't you watching?

15:00.858 --> 15:02.151
I've seen it plenty of times.

15:04.570 --> 15:07.781
So, you changed the ending.

15:10.701 --> 15:12.494
It's about us, isn't it?

15:13.787 --> 15:15.080
Are you upset?

15:15.497 --> 15:18.918
No, I'm the opposite of upset.

15:19.001 --> 15:21.754
-I love it, Luke.
-[exhales]

15:22.254 --> 15:23.422
Cool.

15:25.758 --> 15:27.885
And I saw our parents in the balcony.

15:27.968 --> 15:29.428
It's pretty cute. [chuckles]

15:30.262 --> 15:33.223
If you saw what I saw,
you wouldn't be calling it cute.

15:33.515 --> 15:34.683
[chuckles]

15:40.564 --> 15:42.024
Wanna head back in?

15:42.608 --> 15:44.151
Yeah, it's pretty much over.

15:45.319 --> 15:47.446
And that was a friend-kiss, by the way.

15:47.529 --> 15:50.074
I-I know, Kate. I-I know.

15:50.157 --> 15:52.242
[McQuaid]<i> Get him!</i>

15:52.326 --> 15:54.328
[audience laughing]

15:54.411 --> 15:56.288
[McQuaid]<i> Damn you, Agent Smith!</i>

16:01.543 --> 16:03.128
-[grunts]
-[McQuaid laughs]

16:05.172 --> 16:06.465
<i>Yo, blueberry!</i>

16:08.801 --> 16:10.177
<i>Let's jam.</i>

16:12.179 --> 16:13.681
[all] Whoa!

16:14.682 --> 16:16.475
[laughing]

16:16.558 --> 16:18.227
[audience cheering]

16:24.108 --> 16:25.401
Whoo!

16:32.574 --> 16:33.701
[audience whistling]

16:36.787 --> 16:37.788
Go, Luke!

16:40.249 --> 16:41.375
Whoo!

16:42.835 --> 16:45.379
[Scott] Holy crap, that movie was awesome!

16:45.462 --> 16:48.716
-We've got to make another one.
-A courtroom drama next time!

16:48.799 --> 16:50.009
It'd be so exciting.

16:50.092 --> 16:52.261
We should make an Italian slasher movie.

16:52.344 --> 16:53.262
-Ah!
-Nice.

16:53.345 --> 16:55.472
No, as if.

16:56.640 --> 16:57.933
Hey.

16:58.267 --> 16:59.309
Hey.

17:00.227 --> 17:01.979
-That for me?
-Yeah.

17:04.606 --> 17:07.484
-You wanna...
-What?

17:09.945 --> 17:11.155
Come with me.

17:15.034 --> 17:17.286
Oh, this cake is incredible.

17:19.621 --> 17:20.789
Hey.

17:22.124 --> 17:23.208
Are you McQuaid?

17:23.292 --> 17:26.086
Yeah, yeah, he's McQuaid.
And I'm Tyler.

17:26.170 --> 17:27.755
Will you sign my program?

17:27.838 --> 17:29.965
Um, what? Why?

17:30.049 --> 17:32.009
You were the funniest part of the movie.

17:32.926 --> 17:35.846
Yeah, I'm usually much better
at detecting sarcasm.

17:36.555 --> 17:38.182
[giggling] See? He's so funny.

17:42.394 --> 17:44.480
Okay. I'm going in.

17:49.777 --> 17:52.321
[stammering]
I-I-I'll sign it, if you want.

17:52.404 --> 17:54.531
["Lovefool" by The Cardigans playing]

17:54.615 --> 17:59.661
<i>♪ That I ought to stick to another man ♪</i>

17:59.745 --> 18:03.290
<i>♪ A man that surely deserves me ♪</i>

18:03.373 --> 18:05.501
<i>♪ But I think you do! ♪</i>

18:07.503 --> 18:11.465
<i>♪ So I cry, I pray and I beg ♪</i>

18:11.548 --> 18:13.550
<i>♪ Love me, love me ♪</i>

18:13.634 --> 18:16.011
<i>♪ Say that you love me ♪</i>

18:16.095 --> 18:17.930
<i>♪ Fool me, fool me ♪</i>

18:18.013 --> 18:20.682
<i>♪ Go on and fool me ♪</i>

18:21.642 --> 18:24.186
[woman] How did you make
the watermelon explode?

18:24.269 --> 18:28.107
Well, basically, my friend Tyler
filled this watermelon full of fireworks

18:28.190 --> 18:29.942
and then we just blew it up.

18:30.025 --> 18:31.151
I mean, it was...

18:33.153 --> 18:35.614
Can you give me one second?
Thanks for coming.

18:38.242 --> 18:40.244
-Hey, little man.
-Hi.

18:41.036 --> 18:43.622
It was so good. [laughs]
I am just so proud of you.

18:43.705 --> 18:44.957
